13 dead after bus plunges into valley in Xinjiang
2013-06-18 23:29:13 GMT
Thirteen people were killed after a tourist bus plunged into a valley on Tuesday in northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, according to local traffic police.The bus was carrying 36 passengers, and the other 23 people were wounded.The accident happened around 5:00 p.m. when the bus was travelling to a tourist spot near the city of Changji, said Shi Rui, a traffic police officer. "The injured have been rushed to hospital," Shi said.Heavy fog was blamed, causing bad visibility for the driver.
